codex
The core storage bug is confirmed, and several candidates collapse once the actual execution model is checked: `cancelSwapIntent` and `closeSwapIntent` index into `swapList` with a per-creator position but move assets out of the global `nftsOne[_swapId]` / `nftsTwo[_swapId]` buckets. I’m now tightening the remaining set around issues that produce real asset loss, insolvency, or lockup, and separating that from owner-trust or “missing feature” noise.
